        content:
          'The main Responsibility for an ISMS should be carried by the “ISO” (Information security Officer").\n\nWe strongly recommend to define who this is at the beginning of the project, to allow this role to be deeply involved from the start.\n\n**The Information Security Officer has a great responsibility and should therefore have the following skills:**\n\n*   Leadership in the implementation of information security policies and best practices in the organisation\n    \n*   Social Competence\n    \n*   Required expertise for technical questions\n    \n    *   Or: Strong management understanding and the ability to solve technical question with the respective staff\n        \n\n**The tasks include the following:**\n\n*   Development of security concepts\n    \n*   Implementation of internal assessments\n    \n*   Staff training\n    \n*   Contact person for problems and questions\n    \n*   Support of the management by consulting\n    \n*   Implementation of current regulations and measures\n    \n*   Provide employees with knowledge and information',
