        content:
          "**Understand**\n--------------\n\nThe organization must identify external and internal issues relevant to its purpose and which influence its ability to achieve the intended outcomes of its Information Security Management System (ISMS).\n\n**ISO® 27001**\n\nIt is expected that you understand and can demonstrate that your ISMS serves its intended purpose. For instance, an ISMS is typically implemented to strengthen security, meet customer expectations, or comply with regulatory requirements. In most cases, it is driven by a combination of these factors.\n\nAdditionally, it is important to recognize potential hidden influences that may impact your ability to implement an ISMS. These may include third-party dependencies or other external factors.\n\n* * *\n\n**✅ Implement**\n\nWe have provided a set of documents in the documents section of Cybermap to assist you:\n\n1.  **Information Security Policy – Chapter 1**\n    \n2.  **Further Requirements**\n    \n    *   Legal Cadastre\n        \n    *   Interested Parties\n        \n    *   Additional Requirements\n        \n\n* * *\n\n**Implementation Steps**\n\n*   **Information Security Policy (Chapter 1):**  \n    Adjust this document to reflect your organization’s unique context. This includes outlining the general direction and key objectives of your ISMS.\n    \n*   **Identification of Requirements:**  \n    Ensure that this document and its sub-sections capture your organization’s specific situation, including:\n    \n    *   Relevant legal and regulatory requirements.\n        \n    *   Key interested parties and their expectations.\n        \n\nBy customizing and aligning these documents to your organizational needs, you ensure your ISMS is robust, effective, and aligned with ISO 27001 requirements.\n\n4o",
