        id: 14.27,
        slug: "secure-system-architecture-and-engineering-principles",
        title:
          "A • 8.27 • Secure system architecture and engineering principles",
        content:
          "🔎 Understand\n-------------\n\n> Principles for engineering secure systems shall be established, documented, maintained and applied to any information system development activities.\n> \n> **_ISO® 27001_**\n\nSecure system architecture and engineering principles are about building security into information systems from the ground up. This ensures systems are securely designed and operated throughout their development.\n\n*   **Security at Every Level**: Security is integrated into all parts of the system, from the core technology to the user interface.\n    \n*   **Risk Management**: Identify and protect against potential threats, making sure security measures match the specific needs of each project.\n    \n*   **Guiding Principles**: Use key security principles, such as building with security in mind from the start, layering defenses, and not automatically trusting any component.\n    \n*   **Continuous Review**: Keep these security practices updated and ensure they are also applied to any outsourced development work.\n    \n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n✅ Implement\n-----------\n\n**We provided some documents for you that you can find in the documents area of Cybermap:**\n\n*   [Software Development policy](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/software-development-policy)\n    \n*   [Change management](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-policy)\n    \n\n**Make sure to implement as follows:**\n\n*   Check and adjust the Security Principles of Chapter 3 in the Software Development Policy.\n    \n*   If your organization regularly design and implement systems that are not covered by software development, you might want to incorporate further security principles in Change management.",
