          "🔎 Understand\n-------------\n\n> Security testing processes shall be defined and implemented in the development life cycle.\n> \n> **_ISO® 27001_**\n\nSecurity testing is essential to verify compliance with information security requirements during application or code deployment.\n\nIt encompasses comprehensive testing of security functions, secure coding, and configurations, guided by a well-structured test plan. This process involves automated tools, independent acceptance testing, and considerations for outsourced development to ensure a secure and reliable production environment.  \n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n✅ Implement\n-----------\n\n**We provided some documents for you that you can find in the documents area of Cybermap:**\n\n*   [Software Development policy](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/software-development-policy)\n    \n*   [Change management](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-policy)\n    \n*   [Change Management Plan](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-plan)\n    \n\n**Make sure to implement as follows:**\n\n*   Security testing for systems & software that is not developed is covered by Change management in chapter 2.4 & 2.5.\n    \n*   The Software development policy contains test requirements based on development stage / branch in chapter 2. Check these chapter and implement to your [test proced](http://procedure.at/)ure.\n    \n    *   At best, you should implement automatic tests. If this is not possible for your organization, manual test & reviews should be extended accordingly.",
