        content:
          "🔎 Understand\n-------------\n\n> Development, testing and production environments shall be separated and secured.\n> \n> **_ISO® 27001_**\n\nDevelopment and testing environments should be separated based on the organization security requirements. This includes these practices:\n\n*   When avoidable, Production data should not be used in Testing environments.\n    \n*   Tools and interfaces for testing should not be accessible in production environments.\n    \n*   Test and Development environments should be secured equally to production or separated, so no unauthorized access or miss-usage is possible.\n    \n*   The level of separation and structure of testing environments should be identified by an risk assessment.\n    \n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n✅ Implement\n-----------\n\n**We provided some documents for you that you can find in the documents area of Cybermap:**\n\n*   [Change Management Plan](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-plan)\n    \n*   [Risk assessment](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/risk-assessment)\n    \n\n**Make sure to implement as follows:**\n\n*   Check and implement chapter 2.5 & 2.6 of change management to define rules on separation of environments & handling of test data.\n    \n*   Check Risk example #47, #48, #49 in the Risk assessment as an example for an risk assessment to identify if your seperation handling is sufficient. A risk assessment should be conducted and could lead to a more simpler structure (e.g. only test / production) or a more sophisticated handling with several staging environments and such.",
