        content:
          "🔎 Understand\n-------------\n\n> Changes to information processing facilities and information systems shall be subject to change management procedures.\n> \n> **_ISO® 27001_**\n\nChange management ensures vital system changes are methodically planned and executed, maintaining information security through thorough documentation, testing, and controlled implementation, thereby preserving the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of information.\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n✅ Implement\n-----------\n\n**We provided some documents for you that you can find in the documents area of Cybermap:**\n\n*   [Change management](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-policy)\n    \n*   [Change Management Plan](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-plan)\n    \n\n**Make sure to implement as follows:**\n\n*   Check and implement the change management policy\n    \n*   The Change Management Plan can be used to document changes in a basic form, but if there is the possibility to use your existing project or ticket software, consider that.\n    \n*   Ensure that your process considers:\n    \n    *   Planning & approval of changes\n        \n    *   Communication of changes\n        \n    *   Fall-Back-Procedures if a change fails",
