        content:
          "🔎 Understand\n-------------\n\n> Test information shall be appropriately selected, protected and managed.\n> \n> **_ISO® 27001_**\n\nTest information should be carefully chosen to ensure reliable testing and protect sensitive operational data.\n\nAccess control procedures, separate authorizations, logging, and data protection should be applied when transferring production data to test environments. After testing, it's essential to promptly delete production data from test environments to prevent unauthorized use.\n\nAt best, test data does not contain production data to avoid handling of confidential information in test environments.\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n✅ Implement\n-----------\n\n**We provided some documents for you that you can find in the documents area of Cybermap:**\n\n*   [Change management](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/change-management-policy)\n    \n\n**Make sure to implement as follows:**\n\n*   Check and implement chapter 2.6 of change management[.](http://management.in/)\n    \n*   In cases where production data copies are created for testing, we suggest to implement a rule like in the template that ensure this copy is tracked over its lifetime and destroyed / deleted at the end of its lifetime to limit risks of missusage.",
