        content:
          "🔎 Understand\n-------------\n\n> Audit tests and other assurance activities involving assessment of operational systems shall be planned and agreed between the tester and appropriate management.\n> \n> **_ISO® 27001_**\n\nTo minimize operational disruptions, audit and assurance activities on operational systems should be planned and agreed upon with relevant management, ensuring limited, monitored, and secure access.\n\n\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\\_\n\n✅ Implement\n-----------\n\n**We provided some documents for you that you can find in the documents area of Cybermap:**\n\n*   [Audit procedure](https://cybermap.circle.so/c/all-documents/audit-procedure)\n    \n\n**Make sure to implement as follows:**\n\n*   When planning audits, especially technical audits like penetration tests, stake holders of affected and reviewed systems should be included to ensure that an audit does not disturb normal operation.\n    \n*   This may include\n    \n    *   Moving certain audit activities beyond business hours\n        \n    *   Limiting access / move certain data to read only\n        \n    *   Supervision of audit activity by bringing technical experts / stakeholder into the audit\n        \n*   Check chapter 3.1.3 of the audit procedure which incorporates the above.",
